wall.name: Veterans Wall of Honor
wall.description: Honoring our veterans who served our country with distinction

fieldData.name: Michael Covert
fieldData.description: Michael Covert is an IT Director at Riverside and a proud US veteran. With a dedication to service and technology, he brings valuable experience and commitment to his community and his ipads :)

fieldData.name: Army
fieldData.description: The principal ground force, dedicated to defending the nation and securing peace through land-based military operations.

fieldData.name: Navy
fieldData.description: Guardians of the seas, committed to securing maritime freedom and projecting U.S. strength and humanitarian efforts globally.

fieldData.name: Air Force
fieldData.description: Defenders of the skies and space, ensuring air superiority, global mobility, and missile defense to protect the nation.

fieldData.name: Marines
fieldData.description: Elite, rapid-response force, known for courage and readiness, specializing in amphibious and expeditionary operations.

fieldData.name: Coast Guard
fieldData.description: Protectors of U.S. waters, focused on maritime law enforcement, lifesaving missions, and safeguarding national security.

fieldData.name: Space Force
fieldData.description: Guardians of the final frontier, responsible for securing space operations and protecting vital satellite systems.

fieldData.title: Operation Enduring Freedom
fieldData.description: A U.S.-led military campaign to dismantle terrorist networks and remove the Taliban from power in Afghanistan.

fieldData.title: WWII
fieldData.description: A global war between the Allies and Axis, involving invasions, bombings, and genocides across Europe, Asia, and Africa.

location.address: Germany, Soviet Union, Europe, Australia, Africa, etc.

fieldData.title: Korean War
fieldData.description: A military conflict between communist-backed northern forces and US-supported southern forces over control of the Korean Peninsula.

fieldData.title: Vietnam War
fieldData.description: A conflict where the U.S. intervened to prevent the spread of communism, leading to a prolonged military engagement.

fieldData.title: Invasion of Grenada
fieldData.description: A U.S.-led military invasion of Grenada aimed at overthrowing a Marxist government and restoring a pro-Western leadership.

fieldData.title: Gulf War
fieldData.description: A U.S.-led coalition launched a military operation to expel Iraqi forces from Kuwait following Iraq's invasion and occupation of the country.

fieldData.title: Iraq War
fieldData.description: A U.S.-led invasion of Iraq aimed at toppling Saddam Hussein's regime, justified by concerns over weapons of mass destruction and ties to terrorism.

fieldData.title: Bay of Pigs Invasion
fieldData.description: A U.S.-backed invasion of Cuba by Cuban exiles intended to overthrow Fidel Castro's government, which ended in failure.

fieldData.title: Invasion of Dominican Republic
fieldData.description: A U.S.-led military intervention in the Dominican Republic aimed at preventing a potential communist takeover during a period of political instability.

fieldData.title: Invasion of Panama
fieldData.description: A U.S. military operation in Panama to depose leader Manuel Noriega and safeguard American interests, including control of the Panama Canal.

fieldData.title: Siege of Beirut
fieldData.description: A military siege by Israeli forces aimed at expelling the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) from Beirut during the Lebanese Civil War.

fieldData.title: Bosnian War
fieldData.description: A conflict in Bosnia and Herzegovina involving ethnic tensions among Bosniaks, Serbs, and Croats, marked by widespread atrocities and the eventual intervention of international forces.

fieldData.title: Jonestown Massacre
fieldData.description: A mass suicide-murder in Jonestown, Guyana, where over 900 members of the Peoples Temple, led by Jim Jones, died after being coerced into consuming poison.

fieldData.title: Berlin Airlift
fieldData.description: A humanitarian operation by Western Allies to supply West Berlin with food and fuel via air after Soviet forces blockaded the city during the Cold War.

fieldData.title: Intervention in Somalia
fieldData.description: A U.S.-led military and humanitarian intervention in Somalia aimed at addressing famine and restoring order amid a civil war and political instability.
